<p>Problem: When using the 'evolve' extension for Mercurial some changesets are marked obsolete and are therefore hidden for example to the 'log' command, like this:</p>  <pre><code>$ hg log -11: abort: hidden revision '-11'! (use --hidden to access hidden revisions)  $ hg log -12: -T '{rev}' o 27916 | | o 27915 | |\ | o | 27914 | | | | o | 27913 | |/ | | o 27912 | | | | | o 27911 | | |\ | | o | 27910 | | | | | | o | 27909 | | | | | | | | @ 27908 | | | | | | | | | o 27905 | | | | | </code></pre>  <p>Question: Is there a way to specify a range endpoint to represent either a non-hidden changeset or, if the given changeset is hidden (like '-11'), the preceding non-hidden ancestor (in this example '-12')? I looked at the 'revsets' documentation but failed to find a combination which worked.</p>